definitions.definition: A nonacademic , periodical publication which consists of articles by multiple writers on some broad topic or theme .

subdefinitions.definition: A radio or television show where each episode comprises a variety of features or segments , akin to the format of a print magazine.
The portion of a warship where munitions are stored .
examples: The cruiser blew up when a shell hit its magazine .

definitions.definition: A chamber in or attachable to a firearm enabling multiple rounds of ammunition to be fed into the firearm.
A reservoir or supply chamber for a stove , battery , camera , typesetting machine, or other apparatus.
A country or district especially rich in natural products .
A city viewed as a marketing center .
A store , or shop , where goods are kept for sale.
